B1 - Discover weak security implementation

Objective
the goal of this activity is to identify weak security practices in real-world systems.

Method
i observed common digital systems, campus infrastructure, and real-world security practices to identify vulnerabilities

Findings
1. password-only authentication systems - many systems rely only on usernames and passwords without multi-factor authentication, increasing the risk of account compromise
2. HTTP websites without encryption - some websites still use HTTP instead of HTTPS, meaning data transmitted can potentially be intercepted
3. single-factor physical access cards - campus access control systems relying only on swipe cards can be compromised if the card is lost or stolen
4. outdated software versions - some systems or applications may not be regularly updated, leaving known vulnerabilities unpatched
5. public wifi security weaknesses - public or campus wifi networks can expose users to interception risks if proper encryption or safeguards are not enforced

Security principle
these weaknesses impact core cybsersecurity principles including:
- confidentiality (data exposure risks)
- authentication (weak user verification)
- integrity (risk of data tampering)
- access control (unauthorised entry risks)

